how do you make a white chocolate cake yum enjoy white chocolate cake lb white chocolate coarsely chopped c boiling water c butter softened c sugar eggs separated tsp vanilla extract c sifted cake flour tsp baking soda c buttermilk coconut pecan frosting combine chocolate and water stirring until chocolate melts set aside cream butter gradually add sugar beating well at medium speed of an electric mixer add egg yolks one at a time beating well after each addition stir in white chocolate mixture and vanilla combine flour and soda add to chocolate mixture alternately with buttermilk beginning and ending with flour mixture beat egg whites at room temperature until stiff peaks form fold into chocolate mixture pour into well greased and floured inch round cake pans bake at degrees for minutes or until a wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean cool in pans minutes remove from pans and cool completely on wire racks spread coconut pecan frosting between layers on top and sides of cake yields one layer cake Bread Cake Cookie Japanese cuisine Chocolate Ice cream Dairy Baked Alaska Brewery Cold Stone Creamery Coffee Pancake Halva Jewish cuisine Breakfast Tea Polish cuisine Flour Pizza Cuisine of the Southern United States Rice pudding Puff pastry Cuisine of the Philippines Idli Maple syrup Mooncake Cuisine of Denmark Sugar Cuisine of Singapore Bagel Horehound Casting Bengali cuisine Cookware and bakeware Textile manufacturing Cheesecake Souffl__ In-N-Out Burger Vinegar Bacon Steel Barbecue Mayonnaise Cocoa Baklava Soap Pudding Turkish Delight Carbon dioxide Biscuit Yerba mate Soy protein Oreo Vanilla German cuisine Roux Peanut butter Rum Agar plate French toast Wine making Dairy product Toffee Confectionery Cha chaan teng Dosa Cuisine of Brazil Red velvet cake Sodium Soft drink Custard Twinkie Soup Chili con carne Baking powder Cider Milk Aluminium Twix Wok Yoghurt Cocaine Tooth Printed circuit board Cuisine of Argentina Pottery Spark plug Cajun cuisine Mattress Porridg